<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Cychrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viduus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Cychrus viduus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826 designated by Bousquet and Larochelle (1993: 79). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">mega</emphasis>
(large) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">iridos</emphasis>
(rainbow) [feminine].
</paragraph>
